    { question: "What happened to Google Business Profile messaging for plumbers?", answer: "Google permanently discontinued the messaging feature on Business Profiles in July 2024. The \'Message\' button that used to appear on your listing is gone. Customers can no longer send direct messages through Google Maps or Search. However, they can still call you directly from your listing, visit your website, get directions, and — most importantly — read and leave reviews. This actually makes profile optimization even more critical, because with messaging gone, your reviews, photos, and profile completeness are the main factors that determine whether someone taps \'Call\' or scrolls past you to the next plumber." },
    { question: "What is Google Business Profile and why was it renamed from GMB?", answer: "Google Business Profile (GBP) is the free listing that appears when someone searches for a business on Google or Google Maps. You\'ve seen it — the card with the business name, star rating, phone number, photos, and reviews. Google originally called it Google My Business (GMB), and many tradespeople still use that name. It was rebranded to Google Business Profile in 2022, but functionally it\'s the same tool. For plumbers, it\'s arguably more important than your website — because when someone searches \'plumber near me\', the Maps pack appears before any website results. If your profile is optimised and well-reviewed, customers call you directly from Google without ever visiting your website." },
